I’m sure I’ve subjected myself to psychological questions like those that can sum up my personality with the way I form shapes in clouds. There are personality quizzes which they say can determine how long you’re going to live by the shape of your saliva as you spit it out. Only the Dalai Lama  knows how veracious these analytical findings are.<br><p> 
<br> <p> I’ve read that certain color preferences can reveal a lot about you. But what about the colors you despise? I know a lot of people. I also don’t know a lot of people but they don’t count. With the people I know, I have secretly studied the way they convulse when trapped inside a room whose color brings up traumatic memories that pale the vicissitudes of your favorite soap opera heroine. So together with my team of unsuccessful stockbrokers, sophisticated cynics whose faces never wound up on any society page and disillusioned sugar mothers, we’ve come up with a close-to-conclusive personality test. What is so good about this is that if you don’t like what it says about you, you can always say “But I love yellow, even mustard yellow.”
<br><br>
